sentences: Paula Seling (Romanian pronunciation: [ˈpa.ula ˈseliŋɡ], born 25 December 1978) is a Romanian singer, songwriter, record producer, DJ, and television personality.
Paula represented Romania in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010, together with Ovidiu Cernăuțeanu, with the song "Playing with Fire".
Starting October 2011, Seling was a juror and mentor in the Romanian X Factor.
In 2011 she collaborated with Al Bano and Plan D.
The song, written by Rybak, premiered on 30 May 2012.
In 2012, she was chosen by Walt Disney to record the song "My Spirit Flies" ("Chiar pot zbura"), for the Pixar Academy Award-winning animation Brave.
Paula Seling was born in Baia Mare, a city in North Western Romania, on 25 December 1978.
